{% include "header.njk" %}

<div id="welcome">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="welcome-row">
      <div class="welcome-left">
        <div class="slogan">Steep is a Scientific Workflow Management System made for the Cloud</div>
        <div class="buttons">
          <a href="/#download-and-get-started"><button type="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg"><i data-feather="book"></i> Get started ...</button></a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="welcome-right">
        <img src="/images/workflow.svg">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="features" class="container">
  <h2>Key features</h2>
  <div class="row mx-lg-n3">
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="cloud"></i> Distributed</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        Dynamic and scalable execution of data-driven workflows in
        a distributed environment such as the Cloud.
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="rotate-cw"></i> Cyclic workflow graphs</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        Support for cyclic workflow graphs without a priori runtime
        knowledge. Workflows are converted incrementally and on-demand to
        so-called process chains.
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="clock"></i> Capability-based scheduling</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        Optimized, capability-based process chain scheduling through
        parallelization and distribution to multiple agents (i.e. Steep
        instances running in the Cloud or in a cluster).
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row mx-lg-n3">
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="repeat"></i> Automatic failover</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        Crashed workflows can be resumed without loss of
        information (even without a database).
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="cpu"></i> Microservice integration</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        Service metadata allows microservices (also called processing services)
        with almost arbitrary interfaces to be integrated/executed.
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="target"></i> Runtime environments</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        Built-in runtime environments for executable microservices that are
        provided as binaries or Docker images.
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row mx-lg-n3">
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="package"></i> Plugins</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        Plugins let you modify generated process chains, the way agents collect
        results, or add custom runtime environments (e.g. Python, AWS Lambda,
        Web Processing Services).
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="database"></i> Optional databases</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        If you want your workflows to be persisted in a database over a long
        period of time, Steep offers support for
        <a href="https://www.mongodb.com/">MongoDB</a> and
        <a href="https://www.postgresql.org/">PostgreSQL</a>.
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="monitor"></i> HTTP and web interfaces</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        Steep has a REST-like HTTP interface, a web-based user interface for
        monitoring, and can provide metrics to
        <a href="https://prometheus.io/">Prometheus</a>.
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row mx-lg-n3">
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="grid"></i> Kubernetes</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        Tight integration with <a href="https://kubernetes.io/">Kubernetes</a>
        enables optimized resource usage through auto-scaling.
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="server"></i> OpenStack</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        The <a href="https://www.openstack.org/">OpenStack</a> Cloud Connector
        allows virtual machines hosting additional Steep agents to be created on demand.
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="trending-up"></i> Scalability</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        Its asynchronous event-driven architecture allows Steep to
        scale horizontally across multiple machines in your cluster and to
        support complex dynamic workflows with thousands of tasks.
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row mx-lg-n3">
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="truck"></i> Production-ready</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        Steep is very reliable and has been used in production for many years
        to execute workflows from various domains. The source code has a very
        high test coverage.
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
      <h6><i data-feather="github"></i> Open-Source</h6>
      {% filter hyphen %}
        Steep is free and open-source. It is released under the
        <a href="http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0">Apache License,
        Version 2.0</a>. The code can be found on
        <a href="https://github.com/steep-wms/steep">GitHub</a>.
      {% endfilter %}
    </div>
    <div class="col-md py-4 px-lg-3">
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container container-smaller main-content">
{{ contents | safe }}
</div>

